title: "Deadpool"
rating: 9.1
review {
  direction {
    director {
      name: "Tim Miller"
    }
    rating: "Very Good"
    comments: "The direction on a macroscale is very good as it interjects meta humor into traditional comic-book action sequences, and they do a good job laying the groundwork for this movie to be a meta-satire; the direction on a microscale is very good as these scenes really bring out the meta humor and the charaters/relationships; the storytelling is very good as they do a good job jumping from past to present to provide an origin story while also showing how far Deadpool as come on his journey"
  }
